Version 1.0.0 GREEN VALLEY HYDRO, LLC MARKET RATE TARIFF
1. Availability. Green Valley Hydro, LLC (???Green Valley???) will make available electric energy and/or capacity under this Market Rate Tariff for sales at negotiated rates to purchasers with whom Green Valley has contracted.
2. Applicability. This Market Rate Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and/or capacity by Green Valley not otherwise subject to a specific rate schedule or tariff.
3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Green Valley.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of any sale shall be established by agreement between Customer and Green Valley.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Green Valley shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Green Valley???s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Green Valley to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Green Valley???s market- based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Green Valley???s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Green Valley has been granted the following waivers and exemptions in connection with its market-based rate authority: (i) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 regarding the filing of rate schedules, except Sections 35.12(a), 35.12(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of the accounting and related reporting requirements under Parts 41, 101 and 141 of the Commission???s regulations; and (iii) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. ?? 824c, and Part 34 of the Commission???s regulations to issue securities and assume obligations and liability. See Green Valley Hydro, LLC, Letter Order, Docket No. ER00-2924-000 (Aug. 17, 2000). Green Valley may sell available electric energy and/or capacity to Monongahela Power Company, The Potomac Edison Company, or West Penn Power Company (together ???Franchised Affiliates???) under the terms of this Market Rate Tariff, provided that the hourly rate for each transaction shall not exceed the hourly market price index in dollars per megawatt-hour as posted by the Pennsylvania-New Jersey-Maryland (???PJM???) Office of Interconnection on the PJM Homepage for transactions at the Allegheny Power/PJM transmission interface. See id. Hourly rates for all such sales shall be calculated as follows: (a) hourly values shall be calculated from the shortest duration PJM posting available (whenever that duration is not an hour) by dividing the number of period hours into the posted price; and (b) Green Valley will multiply all hourly prices within a calendar month as determined above by the megawatt-hours actually sold to arrive at a total rate for the month for all transactions. See idThe Commission has also granted a waiver of affiliate restrictions in Section 35.39(c)(2)(i) of the Commission???s regulations, 18 CFR ?? 35.39(c)(2)(i), in order to permit FirstEnergy Solutions and its affiliates to share employees that engage in fuel procurement for generators owned by Solutions and its affiliates, including AE Supply, and to permit the sharing of employees that engage in outage scheduling and economic dispatch at generating facilities that are jointly owned by AE Supply and Monongahela Power Company. FirstEnergy Corp., 136 FERC ?? 61,216 (2011).
7. Seller Category. Green Valley is a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a), in the Central, Northwest, Southeast and Southwest Regions and in the Southwest Power Pool. Green Valley is a Category 2 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a), in the Northeast Region.
8. Effective Date. This Market Rate Tariff is effective upon the date specified by the Commission.
FORM OF SERVICE AGREEMENT
This Agreement is entered into this day of , 20 , by and among (???Buyer???) and Green Valley Hydro, LLC (???Green Valley???) in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements herein, Buyer and Green Valley the ???Party(ies)???) hereby agree as follows: Article 1. Service.
1.1 Green Valley agrees, during the term of this Agreement, to sell electric energy and/or capacity to Buyer and Buyer agrees to pay for such sale in accordance with the Green Valley Market Rate Tariff on file with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (???FERC???).
1.2 The terms and conditions of such service shall be (1) governed by the Green Valley Market Rate Tariff, as it exists at the time of this Agreement or as subsequently amended, and (2) terms and conditions separately negotiated and agreed to by the Parties, with respect to sales of capacity and/or energy to a Buyer under the Green Valley Market Rate Tariff.
1.3 In executing this Agreement, neither Green Valley nor Buyer commits to enter into any individual sales of capacity and/or energy to a Buyer under the Green Valley Market Rate Tariff.
Article 2. Effective Date and Term of Agreement.
2.1 This Agreement shall become effective on the date first stated above. However, if the FERC or any reviewing court imposes any condition, limitation, or qualification under any of the provisions of the Federal Power Act which, individually or in the aggregate, Green Valley determines to be adverse to Green Valley, then Green Valley may at its option, terminate or renegotiate the terms of this Agreement in light of such FERC order or court action. Each party will use its best efforts to take, or cause to be taken, all actions requisite to obtain the necessary approvals so that this Agreement shall become effective as provided herein at the earliest practicable date.
2.2 This Agreement shall remain effective until terminated by either Party on written notice.
Article 3. Notice.
3.1 Any notice given pursuant to this Agreement or the Tariff shall he in writing and delivered or telecopied to the following:
If to Green Valley: Thomas J. Kalup, Vice President Green Valley Hydro, LLC 800 Cabin Hill Drive Greensburg, PA 15601 Phone: 724-838-6683 Fax: 724-838-6892
If to Buyer:
_____________________________
3.2 The names and addresses for notice to either Party may be changed at any time by written notice to the other Party.
Article 4. Terms and Conditions.
4.1 This Service Agreement is subject to the Green Valley Market Rate Tariff and any other terms and conditions agreed to by the parties which are hereby incorporated herein.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Service Agreement to he executed by their respective authorized officials as of the date first above written.
